						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I've been on the Ben for MVP bandwagon since the very beginning of this season, although I'm a homer.<br />
<br />
3rd down is the money down for QBs.  No one comes close to Ben.  Haley's helped.  Haley's keeping him alive to be spectacular on 3rd downs.  Ben and Haley are like PB and Jelly.<br />
<br />
Ben is having more spectacular plays this year.  He's making plays no other QB could make.  He's winning games now.  That's the only thing that's been holding him back.<br />
<br />
It's gonna take a 13-3 or 12-4 finish for Ben legitimately to be in the discussion.<br />
<br />
But who cares.  Let's ride this horse to the SuperBowl!!!!!
						</blockquote>
